@startuml workflow-technology-research
!include _standard-style.puml

title Technology Research Workflow - Sequence Diagram

actor User as U
participant "Claude Code/CoPilot" as Client
participant "Coordinator Agent" as Coord
participant "Web Search Agent" as WS
participant "Semantic Analysis Agent" as SA
participant "Knowledge Graph Agent" as KG
database "Knowledge Base" as KB

U -> Client: start_workflow("technology-research")
Client -> Coord: Research workflow request
Coord -> Coord: Parse research parameters

note over Coord: Phase 1: Multi-Source Search
par Documentation Search
  Coord -> WS: Search official docs
  WS -> WS: Query documentation sites
  WS -> Coord: Return official docs
else Best Practices Search
  Coord -> WS: Search for best practices
  WS -> WS: Query community sources
  WS -> Coord: Return community insights
else Comparison Search
  Coord -> WS: Search for comparisons
  WS -> WS: Query comparison articles
  WS -> Coord: Return comparative analysis
end

note over Coord: Phase 2: Content Analysis
Coord -> SA: Analyze gathered content
SA -> SA: Extract key insights
SA -> SA: Identify patterns and recommendations
SA -> SA: Create comparative analysis
SA -> Coord: Return structured research

note over Coord: Phase 3: Knowledge Organization
Coord -> KG: Organize research results
loop for each technology aspect
  KG -> KB: Store technology insights
  KG -> KB: Create comparison entities
  KG -> KB: Link related concepts
end
KG -> Coord: Confirm organization

Coord -> Client: Return research report
Client -> U: Display comprehensive analysis

U -> Client: search_knowledge("technology comparison")
Client -> KG: Search for comparisons
KG -> KB: Query comparative data
KB -> KG: Return organized results
KG -> Client: Formatted comparison
Client -> U: Show technology insights

@enduml